# Diagnostics layer rules

## Module ownership

- `quick_test.py` — Implements `--quick-test`: preflight checks + focused pytest subset + live 10-URL BFS crawl + workbook audit.
- `full_smoke_test.py` — Implements `--full-smoke-test`: pre-export gate at representative sitemap scale (mocked crawl).
- `full_smoke_fixtures.py` — Deterministic, index-seeded synthetic fixtures for `full_smoke_test.py` (homepage stays pristine; deeper pages get seeded issues).
- `integration_validator.py` — Implements `--validate`: credential/environment validation only, no crawl.

## Shipped CLI features, not test helpers

These modules are **shipped package features** importable from `main.py`, not developer-only test utilities — treat API changes here with the same care as any other public CLI surface.

## Claude-side entry points

The same gates are exposed to Claude Code via `.claude/commands/quick-test.md`, `.claude/commands/smoke-test.md`, `.claude/commands/validate.md`, and `.claude/commands/preflight.md`. Keep this rule and those files describing the same behaviour — update both sides together when flags or gate semantics change.
